giving the impression to the country

1033
00:58:29.172 --> 00:58:32.592
that these people were out of control

1034
00:58:32.675 --> 00:58:35.803
because they used this substance.

1035
00:58:35.887 --> 00:58:41.601
"These people deserve no help from us
because they use this substance.

1036
00:58:42.060 --> 00:58:44.604
These people we can disregard."

1037
00:58:45.230 --> 00:58:47.315
That's why it's so dangerous.

1038
00:58:47.398 --> 00:58:49.108
♪ Your mama's on crack rock ♪

1039
00:58:49.192 --> 00:58:50.777
♪ You got my mama beat ♪

1040
00:58:50.860 --> 00:58:53.071
♪ Your mama's on crack rock ♪

1041
00:58:53.154 --> 00:58:55.448
♪ 'Cause she's a crackhead ♪

1042
00:58:56.491 --> 00:58:58.493
[Bandele] When you say
that somebody uses crack.

1043
00:58:58.576 --> 00:59:00.745
you don't have to talk
about anything else.

1044
00:59:00.828 --> 00:59:03.039
You don't have to talk
about the lost jobs.

1045
00:59:03.122 --> 00:59:06.125
You don't have to talk about
if someone's been sexually assaulted

1046
00:59:06.209 --> 00:59:07.460
and is self-medicating.

1047
00:59:07.544 --> 00:59:10.255
You don't have to talk about anything.

1048
00:59:10.338 --> 00:59:11.798
You can throw away.

1049
00:59:11.881 --> 00:59:15.927
We agreed that some of our people
were worthy of being thrown away.

1050
00:59:16.010 --> 00:59:17.845
And that's what happened on our watch.

1051
00:59:18.471 --> 00:59:21.933
[reporter 1] Since crack appeared.
thousands of residents in the Bronx

1052
00:59:22.016 --> 00:59:24.269
have worked to demand
more police protection

1053
00:59:24.352 --> 00:59:27.272
to drive drug dealers
out of their neighborhoods.

1054
00:59:27.355 --> 00:59:29.566
[crowd chants] Down with dope!
Up with hope!

1055
00:59:29.649 --> 00:59:32.026
[reporter 2] In Florida.
citizens protest against drugs

1056
00:59:32.110 --> 00:59:34.279
and in favor of law enforcement.

1057
00:59:34.362 --> 00:59:35.822
sending dealers the message.

1058
00:59:35.905 --> 00:59:36.739
Down with dope!

1059
00:59:36.823 --> 00:59:38.950
[Hart] You got people
in the Black community

1060
00:59:39.033 --> 00:59:40.660
saying something has to be done.

1061
00:59:41.911 --> 00:59:44.455
Crack kills! Crack kills!

1062
00:59:44.539 --> 00:59:47.625
[reporter 3] In Miami. at the request
of church and civic groups.

1063
00:59:47.709 --> 00:59:51.254
police added
special anti-crack motorcycle patrols.

1064
00:59:51.838 --> 00:59:54.382
-You're glad to see them. though?
-Yes. Yes. I am.

1065
00:59:54.507 --> 00:59:56.759
Somebody has to do something.

1066
00:59:56.843 --> 00:59:58.970
Hey. pusher! Hey. you!

1067
00:59:59.053 --> 01:00:01.097
Black men out here are watching you.

1068
01:00:01.180 --> 01:00:03.182
Hey. pusher! Hey. you!

1069
01:00:03.266 --> 01:00:05.852
[Butts] People were frightened.
They didn't know what else to do.

1070
01:00:06.978 --> 01:00:09.314
When you're surrounded
by that much violence.

1071
01:00:09.397 --> 01:00:10.607
that much ugliness...

1072
01:00:12.066 --> 01:00:15.903
They resort to what they think
will stop the madness.

1073
01:00:17.947 --> 01:00:21.326
If I had my way.
I'd borrow the Ringling Brothers' cages

1074
01:00:21.409 --> 01:00:25.622
and cage these drug pushers
and exhibit them in all the neighborhoods

1075
01:00:25.705 --> 01:00:29.125
so the kids can see scum.
That's what they are. scum.

1076
01:00:31.085 --> 01:00:35.590
[Hart] We have our congressman
from Harlem. Charlie Rangel at the time.

1077
01:00:35.673 --> 01:00:37.091
and he's telling Ronald Reagan.

1078
01:00:37.175 --> 01:00:39.385
"You're not doing enough
for the Black community.

1079
01:00:39.469 --> 01:00:40.678
You don't care about us."

1080
01:00:40.762 --> 01:00:42.513
In order to win a war.

1081
01:00:42.597 --> 01:00:46.142
you have to have the resources.
and resources cost money.

1082
01:00:46.225 --> 01:00:48.645
And there's no question in anybody's mind

1083
01:00:48.728 --> 01:00:51.814
that the American people
are prepared to pay for it.

1084
01:00:52.440 --> 01:00:54.651
[Rangel] Lock them up.
get them off the street.

1085
01:00:54.734 --> 01:00:59.364
There was no question in my mind
at that time the community was behind it.

1086
01:00:59.447 --> 01:01:01.282
And the ministers...

1087
01:01:02.492 --> 01:01:05.620
they would just raise hell
with the politicians.

1088
01:01:05.703 --> 01:01:09.749
"Why have we elected you?"
"Why aren't our streets safer?"

1089
01:01:09.832 --> 01:01:13.044
You can buy crack
when you can't buy a bottle of milk.

1090
01:01:13.127 --> 01:01:15.338
And I'm saying sentence them for life.

1091
01:01:15.421 --> 01:01:16.547
[crowd] No more crack!

1092
01:01:16.631 --> 01:01:17.965
We want our building back!

1093
01:01:18.049 --> 01:01:19.967
No more drugs! No more crack!

1094
01:01:20.051 --> 01:01:21.636
[Butts] It was so crazy...

1095
01:01:22.512 --> 01:01:26.099
parents would beg
to lock their own children up...

1096
01:01:27.392 --> 01:01:31.187
because they were out here
dealing in drugs.

1097
01:01:31.270 --> 01:01:33.356
People have to take a stand.
like we're doing.

1098
01:01:33.439 --> 01:01:35.358
If they want drugs
out of the neighborhood.

1099
01:01:35.441 --> 01:01:36.776
they've got to take a stand.

1100
01:01:36.859 --> 01:01:38.861
[crowd continues chanting]

1101
01:01:39.404 --> 01:01:42.073
[Hart] So. the community think it's wrong.

1102
01:01:42.156 --> 01:01:46.035
politicians think it's wrong.
Republicans and Democrats.

1103
01:01:46.119 --> 01:01:48.329
I mean. it was a politician's wet dream.

1104
01:01:48.413 --> 01:01:53.626
It's sleazebags of greed and slime
that make millions.

1105
01:01:53.710 --> 01:01:56.713
Our children are gonna
continue to be exposed

1106
01:01:56.796 --> 01:02:01.259
to that horrible.
horrible new concoction called crack.

1107
01:02:01.342 --> 01:02:04.387
Cocaine used to be
the exclusive pastime of the wealthy.

1108
01:02:04.470 --> 01:02:06.723
Now. it can be bought
with allowance money.

1109
01:02:07.682 --> 01:02:11.227
So. it's 1986.
There's gonna be an election.

1110
01:02:11.310 --> 01:02:14.897
All the members of the House
of Representatives are up for re-election.

1111
01:02:14.981 --> 01:02:15.940
And now.

1112
01:02:16.566 --> 01:02:21.779
"The War on Drugs is an opportunity
to talk about how tough I am."

1113
01:02:23.322 --> 01:02:25.908
The Speaker of the House is Tip O'Neill.

1114
01:02:25.992 --> 01:02:30.371
And he says.
"I want a comprehensive anti-drug bill."

1115
01:02:30.955 --> 01:02:33.207
And he wants it done in four weeks.

1116
01:02:33.291 --> 01:02:37.837
so that members can go campaign
on what they've accomplished.

1117
01:02:37.920 --> 01:02:39.589
How tough they've been.

1118
01:02:39.672 --> 01:02:42.383
How to stop this plague in its tracks.

1119
01:02:42.467 --> 01:02:43.718
If I had my way.

1120
01:02:43.801 --> 01:02:48.389
I would take all the drug pushers.
take Alcatraz.

1121
01:02:48.473 --> 01:02:52.894
and send them there for life
without the privilege of any visitors.

1122
01:02:53.770 --> 01:02:57.815
[Sterling] It's hard. generally.
for the public to appreciate

1123
01:02:57.899 --> 01:03:04.113
how long it takes for a bill to go from
first being introduced to finally passing

1124
01:03:04.197 --> 01:03:06.866
the House and the Senate
and being signed by the President.

1125
01:03:06.949 --> 01:03:10.119
In Washington. it might take years.

1126
01:03:10.203 --> 01:03:11.496
[all applauding]

1127
01:03:11.579 --> 01:03:14.499
[Sterling] But Tip O'Neill wants this done
in four weeks.

1128
01:03:15.500 --> 01:03:17.794
So. in that window.

1129
01:03:17.877 --> 01:03:21.464
in pretty much the last week. it comes up.

1130
01:03:21.547 --> 01:03:27.512
"Let's write these mandatory minimums
and throw the book at these dope dealers."

1131
01:03:28.054 --> 01:03:31.599
Today. it gives me great pleasure
to sign legislation

1132
01:03:31.682 --> 01:03:34.769
that reflects the total commitment
of the American people

1133
01:03:34.852 --> 01:03:37.814
and their government
to fight the evil of drugs.

1134
01:03:37.897 --> 01:03:39.899
[crowd applauding]

1135
01:03:44.445 --> 01:03:48.407
It was the most unjust federal law
ever written.

1136
01:03:48.950 --> 01:03:52.870
It has a ratio of powder cocaine...

1137
01:03:53.579 --> 01:03:56.123
100 grams gets you a certain sentence.

1138
01:03:56.207 --> 01:03:58.876
one gram of crack
gets you the same sentence.

1139
01:04:00.962 --> 01:04:05.299
If you've seen a sugar packet
in the restaurant. that's one gram.

1140
01:04:05.800 --> 01:04:08.594
There's a tiny amount of stuff.

1141
01:04:09.136 --> 01:04:15.268
Five of those tiny amounts of crack
would get you a minimum of five years.

1142
01:04:15.351 --> 01:04:20.690
up to 40 years
under the legislation that passed.

1143
01:04:22.400 --> 01:04:27.280
Five grams of crack.
500 grams of powder cocaine...

1144
01:04:27.989 --> 01:04:29.240
the same sentence.

1145
01:04:31.075 --> 01:04:32.827
Many people thought.

1146
01:04:33.369 --> 01:04:36.414
"Well. that must be because

1147
01:04:36.497 --> 01:04:43.004
Congress thought that crack was 100 times
more dangerous than powder cocaine."

1148
01:04:43.087 --> 01:04:43.921
No.

1149
01:04:44.005 --> 01:04:47.550
This was a feature of the haste
with which we wrote this.

1150
01:04:47.633 --> 01:04:52.889
So fast we're not even thinking straight
about what we're trying to accomplish.

1151
01:04:52.972 --> 01:04:54.223
It was a screw-up.

1152
01:04:54.307 --> 01:04:57.560
It was screw-up on top of screw-up
on top of screw-up.

1153
01:04:58.144 --> 01:05:00.271
That happened in 1986.

1154
01:05:00.354 --> 01:05:03.190
And that law targeted "traffickers".

1155
01:05:03.274 --> 01:05:07.486
That's... 1988. they extended that law

1156
01:05:07.570 --> 01:05:11.324
to include anybody
who possessed crack-cocaine.

1157
01:05:11.991 --> 01:05:14.577
The decision in the 1988 legislation

1158
01:05:14.660 --> 01:05:17.622
to associate a mandatory minimum penalty

1159
01:05:17.705 --> 01:05:20.958
with the possession
of a small amount of crack-cocaine

1160
01:05:21.042 --> 01:05:24.003
was part of a larger shift and a decision

1161
01:05:24.086 --> 01:05:26.672
on the part of officials
in the Reagan administration

1162
01:05:26.756 --> 01:05:29.008
to criminalize drug abusers.

1163
01:05:29.091 --> 01:05:33.095
and specifically to criminalize
people who abused crack.

1164
01:05:34.221 --> 01:05:38.059
[sighs] The thinking
at the time was that...

1165
01:05:39.310 --> 01:05:42.939
crack... was being used...

1166
01:05:44.315 --> 01:05:48.069
more openly in the Black community.

1167
01:05:48.152 --> 01:05:51.530
and cocaine was a secret drug

1168
01:05:51.614 --> 01:05:55.493
that middle class people used
that didn't hurt anybody.

1169
01:05:55.576 --> 01:05:58.496
They weren't mugging. they weren't
killing. they weren't robbing.

1170
01:05:59.163 --> 01:06:05.670
The whole idea. if you could concentrate
on where the most damage to society was...

1171
01:06:06.420 --> 01:06:09.632
And it was overkill.
Clearly. it was overkill.

1172
01:06:09.715 --> 01:06:11.926
There was no justification.

1173
01:06:12.510 --> 01:06:15.179
And I guess the best answer to it...

1174
01:06:16.389 --> 01:06:19.642
is an oft-time phrase that you've heard.

1175
01:06:19.725 --> 01:06:22.186
"Seemed like a good idea at the time."

1176
01:06:26.357 --> 01:06:30.569
I. George Herbert Walker Bush.
do solemnly swear...

1177
01:06:30.653 --> 01:06:32.655
"I will faithfully execute the office...."

1178
01:06:32.738 --> 01:06:35.032
[Michael Isikoff] In 1989.

1179
01:06:35.116 --> 01:06:37.952
the polls show that drugs were

1180
01:06:38.035 --> 01:06:42.123
the number-one issue
that the public was concerned about.

1181
01:06:42.748 --> 01:06:45.960
So. George H.W. Bush had come into office

1182
01:06:46.043 --> 01:06:52.967
vowing to crack down on the drug epidemic
that was confronting the country.

1183
01:06:53.050 --> 01:06:54.885
[Bush] My friends. we have work to do.

1184
01:06:55.636 --> 01:07:00.599
There are those who cannot free themselves
of enslavement to whatever addiction.

1185
01:07:00.683 --> 01:07:05.312
drugs. welfare.
the demoralization that rules the slums.

1186
01:07:05.396 --> 01:07:09.525
[Isikoff] Remember. George H.W. Bush
was Reagan's vice president.

1187
01:07:09.608 --> 01:07:13.863
He actually had been
in charge of anti-drug operations

1188
01:07:13.946 --> 01:07:17.867
for the White House in the early years
of the Reagan Administration.

1189
01:07:17.950 --> 01:07:23.164
So. he had every reason to want to show

1190
01:07:23.247 --> 01:07:25.458
he was gonna be tougher than anybody.

1191
01:07:25.541 --> 01:07:28.127
[Bush] There are few clear areas

1192
01:07:28.711 --> 01:07:32.882
in which we as a society
must rise up united

1193
01:07:33.382 --> 01:07:35.134
and express our intolerance.

1194
01:07:35.634 --> 01:07:37.970
And the most obvious now is drugs.

1195
01:07:38.637 --> 01:07:40.181
And there is much to be done...

1196
01:07:40.723 --> 01:07:41.766
and to be said.

1197
01:07:42.266 --> 01:07:46.896
But take my word for it.
this scourge will stop!

1198
01:07:49.607 --> 01:07:52.526
[Levine] The political attention
on the drug issue

1199
01:07:52.610 --> 01:07:54.528
and the crack issue was escalating.

1200
01:07:55.654 --> 01:07:59.742
Drugs become almost the antithesis
of the American way of life.

1201
01:07:59.825 --> 01:08:02.620
Drugs is the enemy that we must destroy.

1202
01:08:02.703 --> 01:08:04.705
[eerie music playing]

1203
01:08:07.166 --> 01:08:08.918
[Scott] I was working with DEA.

1204
01:08:09.001 --> 01:08:12.671
And I was asked to purchase drugs
in front of the White House one day.

1205
01:08:13.589 --> 01:08:18.177
So... I called one of the drug dealers
I'd been dealing with.

1206
01:08:18.260 --> 01:08:19.887
I said. "Come to the White House."

1207
01:08:19.970 --> 01:08:21.514
He said. "Where the fuck is that?"

1208
01:08:23.307 --> 01:08:25.309
I had to actually tell him
how to get there.

1209
01:08:25.392 --> 01:08:28.020
When he came down there.
we sat on the little park bench.

1210
01:08:28.104 --> 01:08:30.022
He gave me the drugs.
I gave him the money.

1211
01:08:30.106 --> 01:08:33.150
You can see the people in the background
going into the White House.

1212
01:08:34.985 --> 01:08:39.782
All of us agree that the gravest domestic
threat facing our nation today is drugs.

1213
01:08:40.366 --> 01:08:43.702
[Isikoff] This was
President George H.W. Bush's

1214
01:08:43.786 --> 01:08:47.540
first national TV address.

1215
01:08:47.623 --> 01:08:49.834
I remember watching it. and. uh...

1216
01:08:50.709 --> 01:08:54.088
the President had this...

1217
01:08:55.339 --> 01:08:58.134
gimmick that nobody expected.

1218
01:08:58.217 --> 01:08:59.135
This...

1219
01:09:00.219 --> 01:09:02.471
This is crack-cocaine.

1220
01:09:02.930 --> 01:09:06.725
Seized a few days ago
by drug enforcement agents

1221
01:09:06.809 --> 01:09:10.354
in a park just across the street
from the White House.

1222
01:09:11.147 --> 01:09:15.651
Lo and behold. George Bush holds up
the drugs I just bought. on TV.

1223
01:09:16.402 --> 01:09:17.778
I almost fell out of my chair.

1224
01:09:17.862 --> 01:09:20.906
It was crazy. I could not believe that.
I couldn't believe it.

1225
01:09:21.657 --> 01:09:22.908
Because it was a setup.

1226
01:09:24.785 --> 01:09:27.204
It's as innocent-looking as candy.

1227
01:09:27.288 --> 01:09:29.999
But it's turning our cities
into battle zones.

1228
01:09:30.624 --> 01:09:33.377
It was a case of political theater.

1229
01:09:33.460 --> 01:09:39.717
The White House manipulating
a real... young kid...

1230
01:09:40.718 --> 01:09:46.223
for political purposes in order
to score and make a political point.

1231
01:09:46.307 --> 01:09:48.350
Here. the rules have changed.

1232
01:09:48.893 --> 01:09:52.021
If you sell drugs. you will be caught.

1233
01:09:52.104 --> 01:09:55.107
And when you're caught.
you will be prosecuted.

1234
01:09:55.191 --> 01:09:58.736
And once you're convicted.
you will do time.

1235
01:09:59.320 --> 01:10:01.864
The White House acknowledged today
that a dramatic moment

1236
01:10:01.947 --> 01:10:04.867
in President Bush's speech
declaring war on drugs

1237
01:10:04.950 --> 01:10:07.912
resulted from a setup
by American drug agents.

1238
01:10:07.995 --> 01:10:11.207
He went there and sold drugs
in front of the White House. didn't he?

1239
01:10:11.290 --> 01:10:12.666
That was the bottom line.

1240
01:10:12.750 --> 01:10:15.419
That's what the man did
and he was arrested for it.

1241
01:10:15.502 --> 01:10:17.755
I hope he's arrested for it. I don't know.

1242
01:10:18.255 --> 01:10:20.007
I can't feel sorry for this fella.

1243
01:10:20.424 --> 01:10:26.472
So. this teenager with no priors.
no record of violence. um.

1244
01:10:26.555 --> 01:10:32.311
ended up spending nearly
a decade of his life in federal prison.

1245
01:10:36.148 --> 01:10:38.525
[bagpipes playing]

1246
01:10:43.572 --> 01:10:47.076
[reporter] More evidence that
the cities are losing the war on drugs

1247
01:10:47.159 --> 01:10:50.537
came as New York's police
buried one of their own today.

1248
01:10:50.621 --> 01:10:54.959
Twenty-two-year-old Edward Byrne
was shot to death early Friday morning.

1249
01:10:56.293 --> 01:10:58.629
[Pegues] The Eddie Byrne story
was a big. big deal.

1250
01:10:59.421 --> 01:11:02.633
You're talking about a rookie cop
getting murdered by drug dealers.

1251
01:11:02.716 --> 01:11:05.886
Just sitting in the car. And he didn't...
He didn't do anything.

1252
01:11:09.807 --> 01:11:14.728
If our son Eddie. sitting in a police car.
representing and protecting us...

1253
01:11:18.440 --> 01:11:19.400
can be wasted...

1254
01:11:21.610 --> 01:11:22.736
by scum...

1255
01:11:24.989 --> 01:11:26.573
then none of us are safe.

1256
01:11:28.033 --> 01:11:30.577
[Styles] What happened to Len Bias
just brought attention.

1257
01:11:30.661 --> 01:11:33.414
There wasn't no real action
from the police.

1258
01:11:34.123 --> 01:11:37.501
But after Edward Byrne
got killed in Queens.

1259
01:11:37.584 --> 01:11:42.172
they were. like. "You killed one
of our police officers because of this?

1260
01:11:42.256 --> 01:11:44.842
Now y'all gonna feel it.
The whole nation is gonna feel it."

1261
01:11:45.384 --> 01:11:46.552
This is a promise.

1262
01:11:47.219 --> 01:11:51.015
The killing must and will stop.

1263
01:11:51.098 --> 01:11:53.684
♪ Woop-woop
That's the sound of the police ♪

1264
01:11:53.767 --> 01:11:56.061
♪ Woop-woop
That's the sound of the beast ♪

1265
01:11:56.145 --> 01:11:58.230
♪ Woop-woop
That's the sound of the police ♪

1266
01:11:58.314 --> 01:12:01.191
♪ Woop-woop
That's the sound of the beast ♪

1267
01:12:02.359 --> 01:12:04.486
All right! I ain't got nothing. man!

1268
01:12:04.570 --> 01:12:08.532
One murder changed
the police departments around America.

1269
01:12:10.284 --> 01:12:12.286
[Styles] Police went crazy.

1270
01:12:12.369 --> 01:12:13.829
They went crazy.

1271
01:12:13.912 --> 01:12:16.373
♪ You can't stand where I stand
You can't walk where I walk ♪

1272
01:12:16.457 --> 01:12:18.792
♪ Watch out! We run New York ♪

1273
01:12:18.876 --> 01:12:21.337
♪ Policeman come
We bust him out the park ♪

1274
01:12:21.420 --> 01:12:23.255
♪ I know this for a fact
You don't like... ♪

1275
01:12:23.756 --> 01:12:27.634
They developed this new task force
that they called TNT.

1276
01:12:28.093 --> 01:12:30.220
[reporter] The Manhattan South
Tactical Narcotics Team

1277
01:12:30.304 --> 01:12:33.432
arrested several drug customers
after buying crack in the park.

1278
01:12:33.515 --> 01:12:36.018
[Pegues] They took
every cop they could find

1279
01:12:36.101 --> 01:12:40.064
and threw them into this unit.
and all day they was doing buy-and-busts.

1280
01:12:40.147 --> 01:12:41.899
We the police. You under arrest.

1281
01:12:44.360 --> 01:12:47.112
The majority of crack users were white.

1282
01:12:47.196 --> 01:12:50.574
but a lot of the people involved
in the economy were people of color.

1283
01:12:50.657 --> 01:12:53.369
And the police specifically targeted

1284
01:12:53.452 --> 01:12:56.872
the populations of color that were
involved in this underground economy.

1285
01:12:57.414 --> 01:12:59.958
[reporter] A massive police crackdown
on crack.

1286
01:13:00.542 --> 01:13:02.294
[Styles] They would make these big sweeps.

1287
01:13:02.378 --> 01:13:05.005
[reporter] The largest drug sweep ever
in a single neighborhood.

1288
01:13:05.089 --> 01:13:07.800
[Styles] And when that swoop comes
and they snatch you.

1289
01:13:07.883 --> 01:13:11.428
if they take ten cracks off of one person.
and you have none.

1290
01:13:11.512 --> 01:13:14.264
they will split it
and give him five and you five.

1291
01:13:14.348 --> 01:13:16.225
-Police!
-[door smashing]

1292
01:13:16.850 --> 01:13:19.103
[Styles] They was coming
at the hood with a vengeance.

1293
01:13:19.186 --> 01:13:21.271
-Okay. okay!
-Put your face on the ground!

1294
01:13:22.481 --> 01:13:24.274
[officer] Crawl! Get down on your hands!

1295
01:13:24.733 --> 01:13:26.652
And from there on. it changed.

1296
01:13:26.735 --> 01:13:29.488
They putting on the cuffs.
your ass was getting locked up.

1297
01:13:29.571 --> 01:13:32.157
♪ Woop-woop
That's the sound of the beast ♪

1298
01:13:32.741 --> 01:13:35.702
[Butts] These kids would be stopped
on the street. frisked.

1299
01:13:35.786 --> 01:13:37.871
They could be thrown into a police car.

1300
01:13:37.955 --> 01:13:40.499
Kept locked up in the system
three. four days

1301
01:13:40.582 --> 01:13:42.960
before anybody knew where you were.

1302
01:13:43.419 --> 01:13:45.921
They said. "You're dealing drugs.
you're going to jail."

1303
01:13:46.004 --> 01:13:48.298
Fifteen. 20. 30 years. Doesn't matter.

1304
01:13:48.382 --> 01:13:50.175
Especially if you're Black.

1305
01:13:51.260 --> 01:13:55.431
[Rodriguez] With the police... they don't
know what the hell they're doing.

1306
01:13:55.514 --> 01:13:58.183
Because they can't differentiate
the good from the bad.

1307
01:13:58.809 --> 01:14:00.894
You guys all look alike.
You all act alike.

1308
01:14:02.062 --> 01:14:03.564
So you all get treated the same.

1309
01:14:06.900 --> 01:14:11.155
I was arrested for being in possession
of a controlled substance.

1310
01:14:11.822 --> 01:14:13.407
And that substance was crack.

1311
01:14:16.660 --> 01:14:21.206
You know. I remember my leg
being pulled on about 3:00 in the morning.

1312
01:14:21.290 --> 01:14:25.836
and woken up to get dressed
to be shipped off to prison.

1313
01:14:26.837 --> 01:14:29.590
Me and about 70 other women.

1314
01:14:29.673 --> 01:14:33.260
put into a large room.
stripped out of our clothing.

1315
01:14:33.343 --> 01:14:36.305
Every part of our body looked at.

1316
01:14:36.388 --> 01:14:40.309
And then chained together
in this long chain and put on a bus.

1317
01:14:41.018 --> 01:14:42.311
Early in the morning.

1318
01:14:44.730 --> 01:14:47.858
And driven off to this place
that I've never been before.

1319
01:14:47.941 --> 01:14:49.443
I don't know where I'm going.

1320
01:14:51.570 --> 01:14:55.199
And as I'm taking this trip.
I'm thinking about my ancestors.

1321
01:14:56.033 --> 01:14:58.744
And I think of.
"What progress have we actually made?"

1322
01:15:03.665 --> 01:15:05.417
[announcer] Ladies and gentlemen.

1323
01:15:05.501 --> 01:15:09.463
the President
of the United States of America.

1324
01:15:09.546 --> 01:15:11.840
William Jefferson Clinton.

1325
01:15:12.758 --> 01:15:15.719
[Sterling] Bush played an important role
in laying the groundwork.

1326
01:15:15.802 --> 01:15:18.514
but Clinton. then.
has to be even tougher...

1327
01:15:19.348 --> 01:15:20.557
because that's the thing.

1328
01:15:20.641 --> 01:15:22.142
People have got to be tougher.

1329
01:15:27.105 --> 01:15:31.193
We will have the means by which we can
say punishment will be more certain.

1330
01:15:32.778 --> 01:15:37.533
We will put 100.000 police officers
on the street. a 20% increase.

1331
01:15:37.616 --> 01:15:38.659
Go! Move! Move! Move!

1332
01:15:38.784 --> 01:15:41.119
[eerie music playing]

1333
01:15:42.162 --> 01:15:42.996
Get down!

1334
01:15:43.080 --> 01:15:46.083
The war on drugs
helped turn the police into soldiers.

1335
01:15:51.755 --> 01:15:54.091
All right. Hold it.
Hold it. Freeze! Freeze!

1336
01:15:54.174 --> 01:15:56.426
[Hinton] Tens of millions
of dollars from Congress

1337
01:15:56.510 --> 01:16:00.806
goes to helicopters
and to militarizing police forces.

1338
01:16:10.816 --> 01:16:15.612
There is restructuring of policing
from ordinary beat cops

1339
01:16:15.696 --> 01:16:18.907
to creating these elite. funded units

1340
01:16:18.991 --> 01:16:21.952
that are given special resources
and special powers.

1341
01:16:23.787 --> 01:16:26.498
[Hinton] We begin to see
a new level of investment

1342
01:16:26.582 --> 01:16:29.918
into targeting
low-income communities of color...

1343
01:16:30.711 --> 01:16:32.462
with policing and surveillance.

1344
01:16:32.546 --> 01:16:36.842
while making sentences
more Draconian and more punitive.

1345
01:16:36.925 --> 01:16:38.302
[explosion]

1346
01:16:38.385 --> 01:16:40.554
[man] My wife and kids are in there. man.

1347
01:16:41.179 --> 01:16:42.764
Oh. my God!

1348
01:16:44.099 --> 01:16:47.311
The federal anti-drug budget
is up to $12 billion.

1349
01:16:47.394 --> 01:16:50.272
So. it's six times what it was
when Reagan started.

1350
01:16:50.355 --> 01:16:51.648
and it keeps climbing.

1351
01:16:51.732 --> 01:16:53.650
[Bill Clinton] When I sign
this crime bill.

1352
01:16:54.151 --> 01:16:57.863
we together are taking a big step

1353
01:16:57.946 --> 01:17:00.782
toward bringing
the laws of our land back into line

1354
01:17:00.866 --> 01:17:02.826
with the values of our people.

1355
01:17:09.791 --> 01:17:13.211
[Hinton] The 1994 crime bill supports
new police officers on the streets

1356
01:17:13.295 --> 01:17:16.340
of not just big cities
like New York and Chicago.

1357
01:17:16.423 --> 01:17:20.886
but smaller cities like your Indiana
and Flint and Stockton. California.

1358
01:17:24.389 --> 01:17:29.603
There's tens of millions of dollars
going into expanding the prison system.

1359
01:17:29.686 --> 01:17:32.272
And that is when
we really begin to see the explosion

1360
01:17:32.356 --> 01:17:34.775
of prison populations in the US.

1361
01:17:37.027 --> 01:17:40.238
[Hart] Incarceration rates
take off under Clinton.

1362
01:17:40.864 --> 01:17:41.990
But then...

1363
01:17:42.908 --> 01:17:47.496
about the same time. '94.
people start to become concerned

1364
01:17:47.579 --> 01:17:51.583
that the people who were
being arrested for crack

1365
01:17:51.667 --> 01:17:53.585
were almost exclusively Black.

1366
01:17:55.671 --> 01:17:57.881
[Murch] Two-thirds
of crack users were white.

1367
01:17:58.548 --> 01:18:02.552
But between the passage
of the Anti-Drug Abuse Act in 1988

1368
01:18:02.636 --> 01:18:05.764
and 1994.
the passage of Clinton's crime bill.

1369
01:18:06.431 --> 01:18:10.185
not a single white person was convicted

1370
01:18:10.268 --> 01:18:13.522
of a federal crack offense in Los Angeles.

1371
01:18:36.211 --> 01:18:40.382
[Murch] There is just massive outrage
in the African-American community

1372
01:18:40.465 --> 01:18:42.008
about mass incarceration.

1373
01:18:42.092 --> 01:18:45.303
and also about the damage
inflicted by the crack economy itself.

1374
01:18:51.226 --> 01:18:54.730
Much of the anger
became focused on the CIA...

1375
01:18:56.022 --> 01:18:59.067
and its role in helping
to create the crack crisis.

1376
01:18:59.526 --> 01:19:01.570
It doesn't make any difference.

1377
01:19:01.653 --> 01:19:04.656
Whether they delivered the kilo themselves

1378
01:19:04.740 --> 01:19:07.117
or turned their heads
while somebody else did it.

1379
01:19:07.200 --> 01:19:08.869
they're just as guilty.

1380
01:19:10.579 --> 01:19:14.958
I am going to make somebody pay
for what they have done

1381
01:19:15.041 --> 01:19:17.836
to my community and to my people.

1382
01:19:17.919 --> 01:19:18.920
[crowd applauds]

1383
01:19:22.466 --> 01:19:24.593
I think the CIA is involved.

1384
01:19:24.676 --> 01:19:27.345
The CIA's been involved
in every ugly thing that's happened

1385
01:19:27.429 --> 01:19:29.139
over the last 20 or 30 years.

1386
01:19:29.222 --> 01:19:30.849
We are your wake-up call!

1387
01:19:30.932 --> 01:19:33.393
[Kornbluh] The crack epidemic
affected the poverty levels.

1388
01:19:33.477 --> 01:19:35.479
the safety levels of communities.

1389
01:19:35.562 --> 01:19:38.148
People's health was affected.

1390
01:19:38.231 --> 01:19:41.401
People's lives were ended or changed.

1391
01:19:41.485 --> 01:19:42.944
People lost their freedom.

1392
01:19:43.487 --> 01:19:45.363
[woman] I'm not bringing drugs
into the country.

1393
01:19:45.447 --> 01:19:47.407
See. there are people in major positions

1394
01:19:47.491 --> 01:19:48.950
-that are doing this.
-Has to be.

1395
01:19:49.493 --> 01:19:51.620
[Kornbluh] So. it is
certainly understandable

1396
01:19:51.703 --> 01:19:55.415
why a community that was
so disproportionately affected

1397
01:19:55.499 --> 01:19:57.918
would rise up in disgust and horror

1398
01:19:58.001 --> 01:20:03.465
at any implication that the US government
was even a little bit involved

1399
01:20:03.548 --> 01:20:06.426
in drugs coming into their community.

1400
01:20:06.510 --> 01:20:08.929
[dramatic music playing]

1401
01:20:10.096 --> 01:20:15.393
Los Angeles was the epicenter for crack
in the 1980s and 1990s.

1402
01:20:15.477 --> 01:20:18.814
Much of the anger in Los Angeles
spills over into the rest of the country.

1403
01:20:18.897 --> 01:20:22.108
and LA becomes the center.
the epicenter of organizing.

1404
01:20:24.528 --> 01:20:30.200
And this organizing ultimately forces
the head of the CIA. John Deutch.

1405
01:20:30.283 --> 01:20:35.247
to come to Los Angeles
and to speak at a high school in Watts.

1406
01:20:37.290 --> 01:20:40.043
The director of the CIA
was in Los Angeles today.

1407
01:20:40.126 --> 01:20:43.338
trying to put down reports
that the CIA. in the past.

1408
01:20:43.421 --> 01:20:47.259
connived to spread crack-cocaine
in America's inner cities.

1409
01:20:50.512 --> 01:20:54.724
[Murch] It's this moment. essentially.
of the community confronting the CIA.

1410
01:20:55.642 --> 01:21:00.689
In Baldwin Village where I live.
there are no jobs for the children.

1411
01:21:00.772 --> 01:21:03.817
And our kids are commodities.

1412
01:21:03.900 --> 01:21:06.403
They're being cycled through the prisons.

1413
01:21:06.486 --> 01:21:07.779
They come back to the street

1414
01:21:07.863 --> 01:21:11.283
and they're marked and scarred
for the rest of their life.

1415
01:21:12.075 --> 01:21:14.828
We are tired and we're hurt.
and we're angry.

1416
01:21:15.453 --> 01:21:18.123
Give us explanations.

1417
01:21:18.206 --> 01:21:22.210
You. the President. and everybody else
should be highly upset...

1418
01:21:23.086 --> 01:21:26.089
and say. "How did this cancer get here?

1419
01:21:26.756 --> 01:21:27.799
How did it happen?"

1420
01:21:28.466 --> 01:21:29.926
[Deutch] Now. we all know

1421
01:21:30.010 --> 01:21:33.054
that the US government 
and the CIA supported

1422
01:21:33.138 --> 01:21:35.181
the Contras and their efforts to overthrow

1423
01:21:35.265 --> 01:21:39.269
the Sandinista government in Nicaragua
in the middle-'80s.

1424
01:21:40.020 --> 01:21:45.775
Now. it is alleged the CIA also helped
the Contras raise money for arms

1425
01:21:45.859 --> 01:21:49.821
by introducing
crack-cocaine into California.

1426
01:21:49.905 --> 01:21:51.865
It is an appalling charge.

1427
01:21:52.407 --> 01:21:54.784
It is a charge that cannot go unanswered.

1428
01:21:55.619 --> 01:22:00.248
I've asked the CIA Inspector General
to undertake a full investigation.

1429
01:22:00.332 --> 01:22:03.793
I think it's pretty evident
that the sentiment in this room

1430
01:22:03.877 --> 01:22:07.005
is that of pain. anger.
and especially that of mistrust.

1431
01:22:07.631 --> 01:22:10.008
How can we feel comfortable
with an investigation

1432
01:22:10.091 --> 01:22:13.219
that's going to be conducted by someone
on the government payroll

1433
01:22:13.303 --> 01:22:15.388
to investigate the CIA in its wrongdoing?

1434
01:22:15.472 --> 01:22:16.556
[crowd applauds]

1435
01:22:16.640 --> 01:22:18.016
This is some bullshit. buddy.

1436
01:22:18.600 --> 01:22:20.268
[crowd applauds]

1437
01:22:21.645 --> 01:22:23.813
[cheering]

1438
01:22:23.897 --> 01:22:25.273
[woman] Wait just a minute.

1439
01:22:30.487 --> 01:22:35.408
[Kornbluh] The CIA's Inspector General
did do a rather large report.

1440
01:22:35.492 --> 01:22:38.870
And. in fact. it did contain
a series of new revelations

1441
01:22:38.954 --> 01:22:41.790
about the extent to which
the CIA either looked the other way.

1442
01:22:41.873 --> 01:22:46.086
knew about.
or collaborated with drug smugglers

1443
01:22:46.169 --> 01:22:48.713
in their quest to overthrow
the Sandinista government.

1444
01:22:49.965 --> 01:22:54.260
The Reagan administration cared less
about cocaine coming into this country

1445
01:22:54.344 --> 01:22:58.014
than they did about waging
an illegal paramilitary war

1446
01:22:58.640 --> 01:23:01.768
against a little country
in Central America

1447
01:23:01.851 --> 01:23:04.562
that basically represented no threat

1448
01:23:04.646 --> 01:23:07.107
to the security
of the United States of America.

1449
01:23:12.404 --> 01:23:15.407
Drugs. of course. do represent a threat.

1450
01:23:21.830 --> 01:23:25.583
If you got a war on drugs...
is it not a war on the people

1451
01:23:25.667 --> 01:23:27.127
that are supplying the drugs?

1452
01:23:27.210 --> 01:23:30.380
Or is it only a war
on the victims of the drug war?

1453
01:23:30.463 --> 01:23:31.923
That was the hypocrisy.

1454
01:23:32.007 --> 01:23:36.261
And... sadly... we never addressed it.

1455
01:23:37.303 --> 01:23:40.223
People died. Communities are ravaged.

1456
01:23:40.306 --> 01:23:43.393
Nothing ever was done.

1457
01:23:43.977 --> 01:23:47.272
We left the communities of color
to be devastated.

1458
01:24:00.368 --> 01:24:03.496
[Burton] I was sentenced to prison
six different times.

1459
01:24:05.665 --> 01:24:09.252
You would have thought
someone would have said...

1460
01:24:11.379 --> 01:24:13.923
that you don't have a criminal problem...

1461
01:24:16.051 --> 01:24:18.428
you have an alcohol or a drug problem.

1462
01:24:19.512 --> 01:24:20.889
And there's help for that.

1463
01:24:23.224 --> 01:24:25.101
But I was never offered any help.

1464
01:24:27.103 --> 01:24:28.938
And I read the papers today...

1465
01:24:31.274 --> 01:24:33.818
and I look
at the approach to opioid use...

1466
01:24:34.903 --> 01:24:36.821
and you hear about a health approach.

1467
01:24:38.490 --> 01:24:40.116
Not a criminal approach.

1468
01:24:41.910 --> 01:24:43.828
I'm 21 years sober now.

1469
01:24:46.164 --> 01:24:48.583
Wasn't I worth an investment in treatment?

1470
01:24:58.968 --> 01:25:00.053
[softly] I'm sorry.

1471
01:25:00.929 --> 01:25:02.055
[sniffles]

1472
01:25:04.808 --> 01:25:07.060
[sighs] For the past...

1473
01:25:10.063 --> 01:25:11.773
20-some years...

1474
01:25:13.149 --> 01:25:15.193
I've been living with PTSD.

1475
01:25:16.861 --> 01:25:18.905
It really started once I got shot.

1476
01:25:20.323 --> 01:25:24.536
And every now and again. you know.
I might have a bipolar episode.

1477
01:25:24.619 --> 01:25:26.329
Mood swings here and there.

1478
01:25:26.412 --> 01:25:28.373
I have anxiety. you know.

1479
01:25:28.456 --> 01:25:31.042
So. I mean. these are things
that I have to deal with

1480
01:25:31.126 --> 01:25:32.877
because of the choices that I made.

1481
01:25:34.712 --> 01:25:35.547
Yep.

1482
01:25:40.426 --> 01:25:42.303
[Styles] I was shot in 1988.

1483
01:25:43.138 --> 01:25:44.097
Five times.

1484
01:25:45.265 --> 01:25:46.975
I went away for three years.

1485
01:25:47.058 --> 01:25:51.229
I got locked up
for gun possession and drug possession.

1486
01:25:52.730 --> 01:25:54.149
I really lost myself.

1487
01:25:56.359 --> 01:25:58.236
I have plenty of regrets...

1488
01:25:59.320 --> 01:26:02.615
for the role I played in the crack era.

1489
01:26:03.158 --> 01:26:04.200
Um...

1490
01:26:04.993 --> 01:26:06.619
I lost a lot of friends.

1491
01:26:07.412 --> 01:26:09.289
A lot of friends. Almost all of them.

1492
01:26:09.831 --> 01:26:11.207
I lost my job.

1493
01:26:12.292 --> 01:26:13.626
I lost my home.

1494
01:26:14.752 --> 01:26:19.132
It made me lose everything.
Everything. And...

1495
01:26:20.550 --> 01:26:23.970
I got to the point
where I didn't care no more.

1496
01:26:24.053 --> 01:26:28.016
Especially after I asked my sister
to take my girls.

1497
01:26:32.061 --> 01:26:34.606
It changed me
from the person that I was...

1498
01:26:36.024 --> 01:26:37.692
to where I'm at now.

1499
01:26:41.946 --> 01:26:43.489
Oh. my God.

1500
01:26:48.786 --> 01:26:50.538
I have to think about my cousins.

1501
01:26:51.873 --> 01:26:52.957
My friends...

1502
01:26:54.584 --> 01:26:57.337
who were put in the system

1503
01:26:58.421 --> 01:26:59.589
before 18...

1504
01:27:00.882 --> 01:27:03.343
because of this thing we're calling crack.

1505
01:27:03.426 --> 01:27:05.428
[sad instrumental music playing]

1506
01:27:11.476 --> 01:27:13.311
[Hart] There's a proverb.

1507
01:27:13.394 --> 01:27:18.274
I went back to my old neighborhood
and I yelled. "Where are my friends?"

1508
01:27:18.942 --> 01:27:21.527
And an echo came back and said.

1509
01:27:21.611 --> 01:27:23.071
"Where are my friends?"

1510
01:27:44.008 --> 01:27:46.010
[ethereal music playing]



